Project Summary
This project is a Microservices-based DevOps system

Docker(Containerization)
Kubernetes(Container Orchestration)
AWS EC2(cloud deployment)
Prometheus(monitoring)
Grafana(visualization)
Redis(Caching)
GitHub Actions(CI/CD)

## Architecture

API Gateway → Port 5000
User Service → Port 5001
Product Service → Port 5002
Prometheus → Port 9090
Grafana → Port 3000

## LOCAL RUN (STEP-BY-STEP)

1️.Run API Gateway
cd api-gateway
npm install
node index.js

2️.Run User Service
cd user-service
npm install
node index.js

3️.Run Product Service
cd product-service
npm install
node index.js

4️.Test Locally
http://localhost:5000/users
http://localhost:5000/products

5️.Run Full System (Docker)
docker-compose up --build

6️.Access
API → http://localhost:5000
Grafana → http://localhost:3000
Prometheus → http://localhost:9090

## EC2 DEPLOYMENT

1️.Connect to EC2
ssh -i /path/to/key.pem ubuntu@<EC2-IP>

2️.Install Docker
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

3️.Install Docker Compose
sudo apt install docker-compose -y

4️.Clone Project
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/devops-project.git
cd devops-project

5️.Run Project
sudo docker-compose up --build -d

6️.Check Containers
sudo docker ps

7.Access in Browser
API → http://<EC2-IP>:5000
Grafana → http://<EC2-IP>:3000
Prometheus → http://<EC2-IP>:9090

## Kubernetes Deployment
Apply all services:
kubectl apply -f k8s/

Check pods:
kubectl get pods

Access API (port-forward):
kubectl port-forward service/api-gateway 5000:5000

API → http://localhost:5000

